    {
      "id": "bass-speaker",
      "categories": ["Object", "Sound"],
      "title": "Bass Speaker",
      "year": 2025,
      "description": "I wanted to see if I could create a minimalist approach to a subwoofer. Creating a simple box with large radius round-over edges, responding to the soft form of the subwoofer shape. The result is a monochrome SUB.",
      "materials": "CNC cut Baltic Birch plywood, epoxy, rubber feet, 3D prints, paint, 18\" subwoofer components, lifting hardware",
      "process": "CAD Design (Fusion 360) — creating a 3D model with recessed and interlocking joints with tight tolerances to fit perfectly together. CNC cutting the plywood, assembly, sanding, painting, subwoofer and sound component installation.",
